article.description: Ray Salnave had 19 points off the bench to lead Monmouth to a 98-92 win over Quinnipiac in the Metro Atlantic Conference Tourney quarterfinals on Saturday night.
article.headline: Salnave's 19 lifts Monmouth past Quinnipiac in MAAC tourney
article.linkText: Salnave's 19 lifts Monmouth past Quinnipiac in MAAC tourney
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Ray Salnave had 19 points off the bench to lead Monmouth to a 98-92 win over Quinnipiac in the Metro Atlantic Conference Tourney quarterfinals on Saturday night. Mustapha Traore had 19 points for Monmouth (13-20). Marcus McClary added 14 points. Diago Quinn had 12 points for Monmouth. The 98 points were a season best for Monmouth. Cameron Young had 33 points and seven rebounds for the Bobcats (16-14). Jacob Rigoni scored a career-high 30 points. Rich Kelly had 10 points and 11 assists. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
